.TH p3d_info 1 "February 2026" "arma-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
p3d_info \- extract structured metadata from P3D files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B p3d_info
.RI [ flags ]
.RI [ input.p3d ]
.br
.B p3d_info
.B --rvmat
.I material.rvmat
.RI [ --pretty ]
.br
.B p3d_info
.B --materials
.I model.p3d
.RI [ --db\  a3.db ]
.RI [ --drive-root\  path ]
.RI [ --pretty ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B p3d_info
parses ODOL and MLOD model files and outputs JSON metadata.
Input can be a file, stdin (
.B -
), or omitted (stdin).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B
--pretty
Pretty-print JSON output.
.TP
.B
--json
Write JSON to stdout instead of files.
.TP
.B
--rvmat \fIpath\fR
Parse one RVMAT file and print material JSON to stdout.
.TP
.B
--materials \fImodel.p3d\fR
Parse a model and list all referenced RVMATs with resolved properties.
.TP
.B
--db \fIpath\fR
Use A3DB to resolve model/material paths inside PBOs.
.TP
.B
--drive-root \fIpath\fR
Use this disk root for case-insensitive virtual-path fallback (for example
.BR P: ).
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help.
.SH OUTPUT
In default P3D mode, when writing files, output is stored in
.BR <input>_p3d_info/p3d.json .
In
.B --rvmat
and
.B --materials
modes, JSON is always written to stdout.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR p3d_odol2mlod (1)
